The paper deals with the localization and tracking of moving nodes in a network, which involves information processing and communication. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the fundamental limits of navigation accuracy, which is a topic related to control systems and system dynamics, indicating that the paper could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces the notion of carry-over information and provides a geometrical interpretation of navigation information, which involves mathematical concepts and visualization, suggesting that the paper could belong to the Mathematical Physics (cs.MA) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
